Private Key:
- Expected components
	- version
	- modulus (n)
	- publicExponent (e)
	- privateExponent (d)
	- prime1 (p)
	- prime2 (q)
	- exponent1 (d mod (p-1))
	- exponent2 (d mod (q-1))
	- coefficient ((inverse of q) mod p)

- Decryption: I used cat on the private-key file and pasted it into the ASN.1 JavaScript
  Decoder
  	- version = 0
  	- modulus (n) = (3072 bit) 
	- publicExponent (e) = 65537
	- privateExponent (d) = (3070 bit)

	- prime1 (p) = (1536 bit)

	- prime2 (q) = (1536 bit)

	- exponent1 (d mod (p-1)) = (1535 bit)

	- exponent2 (d mod (q-1)) = (1535 bit)

	- coefficient ((inverse of q) mod p) = (1536 bit)


Public Key (8017 A.1.1): 
- Expected components
	- modulus (n)
	- publicExponent (e)

- Decryption: I converted the format of the public key from .pub to .pem using ssh-keygen -f id_rsa_homework.pub -e -m pem > id_rsa_homework.pub.pem and put it in the ASN decoder. The result was mixing up the values for some reason though(decoder error?), saying that 65537 was the modulus (I knew it was the public exponent from private key) and that the very long number was the version (which didn't make much sense)
	- modulus (n): (3072 bit)

	- publicExponent (e): 65537

Sanity Check
- Checked if p * q == n (which returned true)

- Checked if (e (public key) * d) % lambda_n == 1 (which also returned true)
